snippet.textDisplay:
Big Black Clock @Sorry to say, but if you say Daler Mahendi WAS a great Punjabi singer and most of all that We The Punjabis love him, that's very disrespectful towards the real great singers. He just went with the flow and gave couple of bhangra pop type hits only in terms of bollywood music.

He also used to take people in foreign countries illegally along with his orchestra and used to take huge sum of money from them. He was known as a "kabootarbaaz".

I know a couple of incidents where he almost got his ass kicked while performing in Punjab due to lack of depth in his music and couldn't entertain the crowd. People don't follow him. Real singers need just their voice to keep the crowd overwhelmed. He hardly performed in Punjab and people don't hire him in marriage ceremonies to sing, because he can't entertain the crowd. Punjabi folks, and I mean real Punjabis who've been in Punjab Villages and small towns don't even recognize him as a singer....dig deeper if you are fond of real good music and you'll get to hear soulful singers everywhere in Punjab, from the past and in the present time.
